                  "key": "gen_ai.output.messages",
                  "value": {
                    "stringValue": "[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"finish_reason\":\"stop\",\"parts\":[{\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":\"Let me define variables:\\n- Let the ball cost x dollars\\n- The bat costs x + 1.00 dollars (since the bat costs $1.00 more than the ball)\\n\\nTogether they cost $1.10:\\nx + (x + 1.00) = 1.10\\n2x + 1.00 = 1.10\\n2x = 0.10\\nx = 0.05\\n\\nThe ball costs $0.05 (5 cents).\\n\\nLet me verify: Ball = $0.05, Bat = $1.05, Total = $1.10 ✓\\nAnd $1.05 - $0.05 = $1.00 ✓\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"content\":\"## Setting Up the Problem\\n\\nLet me define the variable:\\n- Let the **ball** cost = **x** dollars\\n- Then the **bat** costs = **x + $1.00** dollars (since it costs $1.00 more)\\n\\n## Solving the Equation\\n\\nTheir combined cost is $1.10:\\n\\n$$x + (x + 1.00) = 1.10$$\\n\\n$$2x + 1.00 = 1.10$$\\n\\n$$2x = 0.10$$\\n\\n$$x = 0.05$$\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- Ball = **$0.05**\\n- Bat = **$1.05**\\n- Difference: $1.05 − $0.05 = **$1.00** ✓\\n- Total: $1.05 + $0.05 = **$1.10** ✓\\n\\n## Answer\\n\\nThe ball costs **$0.05 (5 cents)**.\\n\\n> **Note:** The intuitive answer of $0.10 is a common mistake — if the ball were $0.10, the bat would be $1.10, making the total $1.20, not $1.10.\"}]}]"
